description:
Wicked, reviewed by Alyssa Mora.

Wicked is a well-oiled machine in the hands of Jon M. Chu. This film adaptation epitomizes what modern movie musicals can and should be, embracing its source material while cleverly translating it to screen. Tear-jerking performances by Ariana Grande and Cynthia Erivo make the movie, playing to their individual strengths to bring to life the rapport between Glinda and Elphaba, who’ll go on to become the good and wicked witches of Wizard of Oz fame. If as many people love this film as much as I did, Wicked will undoubtedly immortalize the Grande and Erivo in movie musical history.

#IGN #Movies
title: Wicked Review

description:
A Minecraft Movie is building it’s publicity push block by block towards an April 2025 release date, and after the divisive reception to the first teaser, we sat down with the film’s director, Jared Hess, and Senior Creative Director of Entertainment at Minecraft, Torfi Frans Ólafsson. We talked about their expectations for the first trailer, what their goals were with the second trailer, and how concerned they were about an “Ugly Sonic” problem of their own.

A Minecraft Movie is set to release on April 4, 2025, but in the meantime for more Minecraft news, guides and coverage, stay right here on IGN.

#IGN #Movies #Minecraft
title: The Minecraft Movie Director Heard Your Complaints: Our Chat with Jared Hess & Torfi Frans Ólafsson

description:
From Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures and starring Jason Momoa and Jack Black, “A Minecraft Movie,” directed by Jared Hess, is the first-ever big-screen, live-action adaptation of Minecraft, the best-selling video game of all time. The film also stars Emma Myers (“Wednesday”), Oscar nominee Danielle Brooks (“The Color Purple”), Sebastian Eugene Hansen (“Just Mercy, “Lisey’s Story”), with Jennifer Coolidge.

Watch the How To Train Your Dragon teaser trailer for the upcoming live-action reimagining of the film that launched the franchise. How to Train Your Dragon stars Mason Thames as Hiccup, Gerard Butler as Chief Stoick the Vast, Nico Parker as Astrid, and Nick Frost as Gobber. The film also stars Julian Dennison (Deadpool 2), Gabriel Howell (Bodies), Bronwyn James (Wicked), Harry Trevaldwyn (Smothered), Ruth Codd (The Midnight Club), BAFTA nominee Peter Serafinowicz (Guardians of the Galaxy) and Murray McArthur (Game of Thrones).

On the rugged isle of Berk, where Vikings and dragons have been bitter enemies for generations, Hiccup (Mason Thames; The Black Phone, For All Mankind) stands apart. The inventive yet overlooked son of Chief Stoick the Vast (Gerard Butler, reprising his voice role from the animated franchise), Hiccup defies centuries of tradition when he befriends Toothless, a feared Night Fury dragon. description:
Don't miss this musical Moana 2 clip from Walt Disney Animation Studios’ upcoming animated sequel. The movie features the voice talents of Auli‘i Cravalho, Dwayne Johnson, Temuera Morrison, Rachel House, Nicole Scherzinger, Hualālai Chung, David Fane, Rose Matafeo, Awhimai Fraser, Gerald Ramsey, and Khaleesi Lambert-Tsuda.

Moana 2 reunites Moana and Maui three years after the events of the first movie for an exciting new voyage alongside a crew of unlikely seafarers. After receiving an unexpected call from her wayfinding ancestors, Moana must journey to the far seas of Oceania and into dangerous waters for an adventure unlike anything she’s ever faced. 

Directed by David Derrick Jr., Jason Hand and Dana Ledoux Miller, and produced by Christina Chen and Yvett Merino, Moana 2 features music by Abigail Barlow, Emily Bear, Opetaia Foa‘i, and Mark Mancina. Jared Bush and Miller are writing the film, which is executive produced by Jennifer Lee, Bush and Johnson.

description:
In today's Daily Fix:
The PS5 Pro is currently the most powerful game console you can buy, but that doesn't mean it's running every game without problems. Some gamers are reporting that several high-profile games, like Silent Hill 2 Remake, Call of Duty: Black Ops 6, and more are having issues when played on a PS5 Pro. Most common is a "shimmering" effect on reflections or walls, and it's possibly caused by the PS5 Pro's PSSR upscaling feature. Sony has not yet commented, and as of this recording, the affected games have not been patched. In other news, Sonic the Hedgehog 3 got a new poster, with more detailed looks like Shadow and, Gerald Robotnik. And finally, The Game Awards nominees have been revealed, and controversially Elden Ring: Shadow of the Erdtree has been nominated for Best Game (weird because it's an expansion to a two-year-old game, and not a standalone game by itself).

#IGN #Gaming #PS5
title: Several Games With PS5 Pro Issues Reported By Players - IGN Daily Fix
